# Comprehensive 2M Tech Audit — Implementation Plan

Full audit of every file in the server, admin, and client codebases for security, logic, validation, code quality, and redundancy. This follows on from the previous audit that fixed 23 issues.

## User Review Required

> [!CAUTION]
> **#1 IDOR vulnerability**: `GET /orders/:id` only requires [authenticateUser](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/middleware/auth.middleware.ts#11-32) — any logged-in user can read any other user's order by guessing the ID. This is a serious production security issue.

> [!CAUTION]
> **#4 Mass-assignment in [updatePage](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/controllers/page.controller.ts#79-97)**: `Page.findByIdAndUpdate(req.params.id, req.body)` — an attacker can overwrite any field including [_id](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/utils/cloudinary.ts#13-21), `createdAt`, `slug`, etc.

> [!WARNING]
> **#8 Bot token leak**: `getTelegramWebhookInfo` directly interpolates `process.env.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` into a `fetch` URL. If the response errors, the token could be logged.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **#16 Error middleware ordering**: In [index.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/index.ts) the global `app.use((err, …))` handler is placed *before* [apiErrorMiddleware](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/utils/ApiError.ts#10-27) at line 220, meaning [apiErrorMiddleware](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/utils/ApiError.ts#10-27) is never reached for errors. Order must be swapped.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **#21 Tax always 0**: [calculatePrice](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/client/src/redux/reducers/cart.reducer.ts#123-145) in the cart reducer hardcodes `state.tax = 0`. If the project has no server-side tax, this is fine. If tax should be calculated, this is a gap. **I need your confirmation on whether you intend to add server-side tax calculation or if zero tax is correct for your market.**

---

## Proposed Changes

### 🔴 Security Fixes

---

#### [MODIFY] [order.routes.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/routes/order.routes.ts)

**#1 — IDOR: any user can view any order**

`GET /:id` currently uses [authenticateUser](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/middleware/auth.middleware.ts#11-32) only. Fix: add an ownership check.

```diff
-router.get('/:id', authenticateUser, getOrder);
+router.get('/:id', authenticateUser, getOrder);
```

The route stays the same, but the **controller** `getOrder` adds:

#### [MODIFY] [order.controller.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/controllers/order.controller.ts)

```diff
 export const getOrder = asyncHandler(async (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
     const orderId = req.params.id;
-    const order = await Order.findById(orderId).populate('user', 'name email');
+    const order = await Order.findById(orderId).populate('user', 'name email');
     if (!order) return next(new ApiError(404, 'Order not found'));
+
+    // Ownership check: user can only view their own orders, admin can view any
+    const reqUser = (req as RequestWithUser).user;
+    if (reqUser.role !== 'admin' && order.user._id.toString() !== reqUser._id.toString()) {
+        return next(new ApiError(403, 'Not authorized to view this order'));
+    }

     return res.status(200).json({ success: true, order });
 });
```

---

#### [MODIFY] [page.controller.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/controllers/page.controller.ts)

**#3 — Debug info leak in 404 response + console.logs**

Remove all `console.log` debug statements and the `debug` object from the 404 response.

**#4 — Mass assignment via raw `req.body`**

Whitelist allowed fields in [updatePage](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/controllers/page.controller.ts#79-97):

```diff
 export const updatePage = async (req: Request, res: Response) => {
   try {
+    const { title, slug, content, isPublished } = req.body;
     const page = await Page.findByIdAndUpdate(
       req.params.id,
-      req.body,
+      { title, slug, content, isPublished },
       { new: true }
     );
```

**#17 — Wrap all page handlers in [asyncHandler](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/utils/asyncHandler.ts#3-8)**

All page handlers currently use manual try/catch. Wrap them in [asyncHandler](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/utils/asyncHandler.ts#3-8) and use [ApiError](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/utils/ApiError.ts#3-9) for consistency and to avoid swallowing unexpected errors.

---

#### [MODIFY] [brand.controller.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/controllers/brand.controller.ts)

**#7 — Regex injection in brand name search**

Escape user input before using it in `RegExp`:

```diff
+const escapeRegex = (str: string) => str.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\]\\]/g, '\\$&');
+
 const existingBrand = await Brand.findOne({
-    name: { $regex: new RegExp(`^${name}$`, 'i') }
+    name: { $regex: new RegExp(`^${escapeRegex(name)}$`, 'i') }
 });
```

Apply in both `createBrand` and `updateBrand`.

---

#### [MODIFY] [telegram.controller.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/controllers/telegram.controller.ts)

**#8 — Bot token leak**

Move webhook info call into the `telegramService`:

```diff
-const response = await fetch(`https://api.telegram.org/bot${process.env.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}/getWebhookInfo`);
+const result = await telegramService.getWebhookInfo();
```

Also remove all `console.log` statements.

---

#### [MODIFY] [banner.controller.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/controllers/banner.controller.ts)

**#14 — `getAllBanners` `includeInactive` has no auth guard**

The `?includeInactive=true` query param is on a public route with no authentication. Fix:

Move the `GET /` route behind optional auth and strip `includeInactive` for non-admins, similar to the product [guardUnpublished](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/routes/product.route.ts#21-32) pattern.

