### 🟠 Logic & Validation Fixes

---

#### [MODIFY] [order.controller.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/controllers/order.controller.ts)

**#2 — `deleteOrder` restores stock for delivered orders**

Stock should only be restored if the order hasn't been delivered:

```diff
-await increaseStock(order.orderItems as any);
+if (order.status !== 'Delivered') {
+    await increaseStock(order.orderItems as any);
+}
```

---

#### [MODIFY] [category.controller.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/controllers/category.controller.ts)

**#5 — Catch block swallows [ApiError](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/utils/ApiError.ts#3-9) in delete**

The catch block around the product-count check catches [ApiError](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/utils/ApiError.ts#3-9) (thrown when products exist) and logs a misleading message, allowing the delete to proceed:

```diff
-  } catch (error) {
-    console.log('Product model not found, continuing with category deletion');
+  } catch (error: any) {
+    if (error instanceof ApiError) throw error;
+    // Product model not available — continue with deletion
   }
```

Apply same fix in `permanentDeleteCategory`.

---

#### [MODIFY] [subcategory.controller.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/controllers/subcategory.controller.ts)

**#5 — Same catch-block swallowing bug**

Identical fix as category controller for `deleteSubcategory` and `permanentDeleteSubcategory`.

---

#### [MODIFY] [utils.ts](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/utils/utils.ts)

**#12 — [reduceStock](file:///e:/MY-PROJECTS/2m%20tech/server/src/utils/utils.ts#4-13) allows negative stock**

```diff
 product.stock = product.stock - item.quantity;
+if (product.stock < 0) throw new Error(`Insufficient stock for product: ${product.name}`);
